  "notes": "Toki Pona (Sonja Lang, 2001; book 2014). Minimal, fully phonemic orthography: 14 letters = 14 phonemes, 9 consonants /p t k s m n l j w/ and 5 vowels /a e i o u/. Syllables are (C)V(n); the sequences ji, ti, wu, wo, nn, nm are disallowed. Stress is always on the first syllable of a word. Written in lowercase Latin (the sitelen pona / sitelen sitelen logographies are not modelled here).",
